# Go Module Version Consistency

All `go.mod` files in this project (excluding `third_party/`) must use the same Go toolchain version.

## Project go.mod files

- `go.mod` (root) — uses the `go` directive directly (e.g. `go 1.25.9`)
- `cmd/wait-for-files-to-exist/go.mod` — uses `toolchain` directive (e.g. `toolchain go1.25.9`)
- `cmd/copy-file-to-pod/go.mod` — uses `toolchain` directive (e.g. `toolchain go1.25.9`)

## Rules

1. When updating the Go version in any `go.mod`, update **all three** files to the same patch version.
2. Do **not** modify `third_party/**/go.mod` — those are vendored and managed separately.
3. After updating, run `go mod tidy` in each module directory.
4. Run `govulncheck ./...` in each module directory to verify no new stdlib vulnerabilities.
